Every facility, workflow, curriculum, and digital platform is engineered in alignment with ISO standards, ILAC frameworks, national legal mandates, and international accreditation benchmarks.

Service Pillars

Accreditation & Quality Mastery


“From framework to formal recognition.”

We guide forensic laboratories, CSI units, and medico-legal services toward internationally recognized standards, including:
	•	ISO/IEC 17020
	•	ISO/IEC 17025
	•	ISO 15189
	•	ISO 21043

Our support includes:
	•	Gap analysis and structured accreditation roadmaps
	•	SOP architecture and documentation systems
	•	Method validation and measurement uncertainty frameworks
	•	Internal audit and management review systems
	•	Pre-assessment readiness and compliance strengthening

We build systems that are compliant, sustainable, and judicially defensible.


